026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=1024%2C572 1024w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=1536%2C858 1536w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=179%2C100 179w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=600%2C335 600w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=125%2C70 125w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=660%2C370 660w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=1000%2C559 1000w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=244%2C136 244w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=1160%2C648 1160w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=170%2C95 170w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=72%2C40 72w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=1200%2C670 1200w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=269%2C150 269w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=537%2C300 537w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=1074%2C600 1074w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=150%2C84 150w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=110%2C61 110w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=285%2C159 285w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=320%2C179 320w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=640%2C357 640w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=800%2C447 800w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/The-Studio.png?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=1280%2C715 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"auto\" data-attachment-id=\"1235101223\" data-wp-size=\"nova_size__sixteenbynine_small_cropped\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e“You’re hearing the first howl of a dire wolf in over 10,000 years,” the team at Colossal said in a \u003ca rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://x.com/colossal/status/1909247817672957959\" target=\"_blank\"\u003estatement\u003c/a\u003e. “Meet Romulus and Remus — the world’s first de-extinct animals, born on October 1, 2024. The dire wolf has been extinct for over 10,000 years. These two wolves were brought back from extinction using genetic edits derived from a complete dire wolf genome, meticulously reconstructed by Colossal from ancient DNA found in fossils dating back 11,500 and 72,000 years. This moment marks not only a milestone for us as a company but also a leap forward for science, conservation, and humanity.” \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eColossal continued, “From the beginning, our goal has been clear: To revolutionize history and be the first company to use CRISPR technology successfully in the de-extinction of previously lost species. By achieving this, we continue to push forward our broader mission on — accepting humanity’s duty to restore Earth to a healthier state. But this isn’t just our moment — it’s one for science, our planet, and humankind. All of which we love and are passionate about. Now, close your eyes and listen to that howl once more. Think about what this means for all of us.” \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
